The paper deals with the construction of RIP measurement matrices in compressed sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of constant weight codes is a central theme in the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under coding theory (cs.CC). The paper proposes a new deterministic construction, which involves the analysis of the properties of constant weight codes, making it relevant to the sub-category of discrete structures (cs.DS). The construction of RIP matrices involves optimization, which is a common theme in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for constructing RIP matrices, which could be considered a new algorithm or technique in signal processing (cs.SI).
